spigot - a rate limiter for aggregating syndicated content to StatusNet
  (c) 2011 Nathan Smith <nathan@smithfam.info>

spigot depends on Python 2.7 or higher and the following non-standard libraries:  

- statusnet from IdentiCurse <http://identicurse.net/>
  (c) 2010-2011 Reality <tinmachin3@gmail.com> and Psychedelic Squid <psquid@psquid.net>
  Bundled with Spigot

- oauth from <http://oauth.googlecode.com/svn/code/python/>
  (c) 2007 Leah Culver
  Bundeled with Spigot

- Universal Feed Parser >= 5.0 <http://www.feedparser.org/>
  
To use spigot, invoke it from the command line
> python spigot

It will prompt you to add at least one account and one feed on first run. For more options, run:
> python spigot -h

